Impacted service: Backup as a Service.

Planned impact:
During the maintenance window, Avamar system ohlpch2bavas001 will be shut down and will remain temporarily unavailable while the DIMM in slot B7 is replaced.

Backup and restore operations managed by this Avamar system will not be available during the intervention.

No active replication configuration was identified on this server, so no active replication activity is expected to be affected.

No data loss is expected.

Main risks:
- Replacement DIMM failure or incompatibility.
- Additional memory errors detected during system startup.
- Extended system unavailability if the server does not complete POST successfully.
- Avamar services failing to start correctly after the hardware replacement.
- Backup or restore job failures if activity is not stopped before the intervention.

Mitigation:
The activity will be performed during an approved maintenance window.

Before the shutdown, the BaaS team will:
- Confirm that no backup or restore jobs are running.
- Validate the Avamar system status and service health.
- Verify the latest checkpoint and maintenance task results.
- Perform a controlled shutdown of the Avamar services and operating system.

The physical DIMM replacement will be performed by an authorized Dell Field Service Engineer.

After the replacement, the BaaS team will validate:
- Successful server startup and hardware initialization.
- DIMM B7 detection and absence of new memory alerts.
- GSAN, MCS, scheduler and related Avamar service status.
- Full system access and readiness for backup and restore operations.
